        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 11:38AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1137 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stephenville, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stephenville, Purves, Harbin, Alexander, Clairette, and Selden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
